5:
So the remaining members of Aegis
are to blame...
9:
Yeah, they've been causing
problems all over the city. Even the
Guild Knights can't handle them on
their own...
11:
I'm guessing their numbers have
increased along with the number of
people with powers.
15: That must be due to the Dragon's Iris.
18:
I received my powers after seeing
the Iris in the sky.
21:
Almost everyone was looking at it,
so I'm sure others are experiencing
the same thing...
31:
Still missing? Yup. And that's
probably another reason Aegis is
getting out of hand.
34:
Some of them are searching for
Tohru, while others have started
their own factions. And now they're
fighting like they weren't comrades
a few months ago.
40: Well, it's not entirely their fault...
43:
We adults failed them when we
couldn't provide them with a safe
and secure shelter...
46:
Perhaps our approach just needs to
change.
54:
I'm the representative of this town.
My name is Seiji Takamori.
57:
If possible, I'd like to have a talk with
you all.
61:
You're jokin', right? Why would we
want anything to do with a stuffy old
geezer like you?
67:
Huh? Wait, aren't you that teacher
from back then?
73: It IS you! Kenny-poo, look who it is!
75: Oh... If it isn't Mr. Crybaby.
80:
So in other words... you want us to
find jobs?
83: I suppose that's one way to look at it.
86:
You all have the choice to live here
or in Palpebra.
89:
If you choose Palpebra, you'll
become citizens of their town. As
such, you will need to work.
92:
And that means going into that
weird Kaleidoscope place, right?
95:
That's certainly one option. Many
jobs from the Guild are on the
dangerous side, but...
98:
Pur Lilie, one of the Guild employees,
will be sure to prepare safer jobs for
you.
101:
All right, but what if we wanna stay
in Shibuya?
104:
Then I'll take responsibility for you.
There will be a few rules, however.
112:
And... If possible, I'd like you to help
me with my work here.
117:
I... want to restore Shibuya to its
former glory.
120:
Luckily, all the infrastructure is still in
place. If we can just introduce
electricity, we'll be able to use
everything again. We just need the
help of scientists and technicians.
123:
Many of them may be asleep for
now, but once they wake up, we'll
have their knowledge and
experience to draw from. Soon, not
just the lights but—
127:
O-oh dear... I'm rambling, aren't I? I
apologize. Those are all far-off
dreams at the moment...
132:
I'm not gonna pretend I understood
any of that, but... If it's you, I'm sure
it'll work out.
134:
For sure! And you'd miss us if we left,
wouldn't you, Teach?
137:
All right, then it sounds like we'll be
working together.
140:
We'll come up with a goal that works
for you. And if there's anything you
don't understand, I'll do my best to
explain it.
143: I am a teacher, after all.
146: ...What if we can't find the answer?
148:
That's fine too. Any decision you
make will surely inform your future.
151:
You're a pretty passionate person,
you know that?
160:
Thank you for watching over me. I
should be safe now.
164:
Guess you noticed us following you,
huh?
167: You didn't exactly try to hide it.
176:
...You're not exactly great with words.
We were just tagging along in case
you needed backup.
179:
Next time you wanna go looking for
trouble, give us a holler.
183:
We just want to help. Weren't we the
ones who asked you to take care of
Shibuya?
185:
I'm just saying, you don't have to do
this alone.
194:
I just... wanted to apologize for not
taking action right away... then and
now.
197:
I'm sorry... I should have been the
one protecting you.
201:
To be honest... I don't remember
much about that time, but thank
you.
204:
Looks like you've finally become the
cool teacher you've dreamed about.
